Model sundowners and skiing example

Britta Grusdt

5/6/2019

knitr::opts_chunk$set(warning=FALSE, message=FALSE)

Get Data

fn_skiing <- file.path("..", "..", "data", "skiing.rds",
                       fsep = .Platform$file.sep)
fn_sundowners <- file.path("..", "..", "data", "sundowners.rds",
                           fsep = .Platform$file.sep)
skiing <- read_rds(fn_skiing) %>% webppl_distrs_to_tibbles()
sundowners <- read_rds(fn_sundowners) %>%  webppl_distrs_to_tibbles()

Skiing example

Prior

distr <- "prior"
skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_cns(distr)

skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_bns(distr)

skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_bn_table(1, distr)

skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_marginal(c("E"), distr)

Literal Listener

distr <- "LL"
# skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_cns(distr)
skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_bns(distr)

skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_bn_table(1, distr)

skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_marginal(c("E"), distr)

Pragmatic Listener

The listener has evidence for variable C (buying clothes); i.e.the distribution of the single bayes net that receives non-zero probability after hearing If she passes the exam, her father takes her on a skiing trip (E > S), is conditioned on C=TRUE.

distr <- "PL"
# skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_cns(distr)
# skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_bns(distr)
skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_bn_table(1, distr)

skiing[[distr]] %>% plot_marginal(c("E"), distr)

Sundowners example

Prior

distr <- "prior"
sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_cns(distr)

sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_bns(distr)

sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_bn_table(1, distr)

sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_bn_table(4, distr)

sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_marginal(c("R"), distr)

Literal Listener

distr <- "LL"
# sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_cns(distr)
sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_bns(distr)

sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_bn_table(1, distr)

sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_marginal(c("R"), distr)

Pragmatic Listener

distr <- "PL"
# sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_cns(distr)
sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_bns(distr)

sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_bn_table(2, distr)

sundowners[[distr]] %>% plot_marginal(c("R"), distr)
